.TH "kmx61_set_mode" 9 "kmx61_set_mode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kmx61_set_mode \- set KMX61 device operating mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kmx61_set_mode
.BI "(struct kmx61_data *data "  ","
.BI "u8 mode "  ","
.BI "u8 device "  ","
.BI "bool update "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
kmx61 device private data pointer
.IP "mode" 12
bitmask, indicating operating mode for \fIdevice\fP
.IP "device" 12
bitmask, indicating device for which \fImode\fP needs to be set
.IP "update" 12
update stby bits stored in device's private  \fIdata\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For each sensor (accelerometer/magnetometer) there are two operating modes
STANDBY and OPERATION. Neither accel nor magn can be disabled independently
if they are both enabled. Internal sensors state is saved in acc_stby and
mag_stby members of driver's private \fIdata\fP.
